    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-02-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-02-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1252"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1252">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">125.0093/2–2849: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in the Philippines</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lockett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Manila</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-02-28">February 28,
                            1949</date>.<lb/>[Received February 28—12:31 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>505. For FA.<note n="43" xml:id="d1252fn43">Division of Foreign Service
                        Administration.</note> Evacuées PU area Monday February 28: State 41; Army
                    none; Navy none; Air none; ECA 8;<note n="44" xml:id="d1252fn44">Economic
                        Cooperation Administration.</note> total 49.</p>
                <p>The PU area will close as of midnight tonight and the remaining evacuees
                    established in quarters in the Military Plaza compound.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lockett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
